$interpreted: Chiyuki: We’re very happy everyone could make it to Kayowai, one of the Fog Sect’s ruined cities, to enjoy today’s games together.
Chiyuki: Today’s victor will nab a guaranteed spot in the tournament finals!
Chiyuki: Now, our contestants have recently been enjoying a relaxing getaway on Hot Spring Street~!
Chiyuki: So, I’m sure they’ll be nice and limber for today’s performance. I hope everyone’s getting excited! But, before we begin—
Excited Spectator: Alliance Beauty! Alliance Beauty!!
Chiyuki: That's right, it's time for the Alliance Beauty mid-tournament tally!
Excited Spectator: Chiyuki!! Chiyuki!! Chiyuki!!
Thrilled Spectator: Come on, don’t keep us waiting! Is that bird winning or not!?
Chiyuki: ...N-No...! This can’t be happening!
Chiyuki: How... I mean, I know the votes were close before, but...
Chiyuki: I don’t believe it~!! I won’t!!
Chiyuki: This can’t be real!!
Chiyuki: (...No... Chiyuki, you have to calm down...You need to have poise, don’t lose it now...)
Chiyuki: (...You have a reputation to uphold. Don’t embarrass yourself! Think of the fans!)
Chiyuki: Ahem... Now, currently in first place is... Puggi!
Excited Spectator: What!? Did she just say what I think she said!?
Chiyuki: Second place is... Hanazono Chiyuki...
Puggi: Hehehe~ As expected, as expected~!
Puggi: First, I’d like to thank my parents for gifting me with this magnificent mug!
Puggi: Especially my mom, for these angel eyes~!!

Wolf Chieftain: Hold on, are you sure you counted right!?
This bird’s got nothin’ on Chiyuki! How’s he winning!?
Puggi: It’s not easy being the main character! Ah, now I’ve got to get ready for the meet and greet, I suppose~

Turtle Chieftain: This is absolute madness! I mean, kids these days!!
They just don’t have any respect for the Alliance Beauty!
Turtle Chieftain: Voting for some damn bird... no respect for tradition! No respect!!
Puggi: Seems like some people just don’t have an eye for real beauty, hmm~
Puggi: I take that as a personal attack! Come on, put up your dukes!!
Turtle Chieftain: Darn... this generation is doomed!
Chiyuki: Ahem, now everybody, I assure you the votes were counted correctly!
Chiyuki: And remember, these aren’t the final results! Nothing's set in stone!
Excited Spectator: Aaaaaaah!! Miss Chiyuki’s smile, it’s melting my heart~!!
Chiyuki: Alright everyone, give a round of applause for our current front-runner, Puggi~!

Puggi: Please, you’re too kind! You’re too kind~
Of course, don't forget about my supporting cast! They try so hard~
Chiyuki: (...Supporting cast? Am I already past my prime?）

Puggi: Oh yeah, where’s Pang!?
He’s not missing my victory speech, is he!?
Chiyuki: Now, I’m sure all of our contestants are backstage and eager to get going!
Puggi: Backstage? How do I get there, this way? Puggi puggi puggi~
Chiyuki: Ah, hold on! Not so fast!!
Soohyeon: Tindoiimu, you’re here!
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: So, just now that soldier came over here and he said, this time...
Soohyeon: ...the Kingdom of the Sun diplomat, Ace, would be our opponent.
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: ......
Soohyeon: Um, Tindoiimu, would you like some hot-pepper candy?

Soohyeon: Some people back at Pearl Manor made it by hand.
It’s not actually too spicy, and it’s really good~
Toyokuni: Pearl Manor?
Toyokuni: But I thought the madame of Pearl Manor went abroad quite a while ago? Shouldn’t it be vacant right now?
Soohyeon: (Oh crap! Soohyeon, you idiot!)
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: Ah, I mean, Seamoon Manor, not Pearl Manor!
Toyokuni: Li Hwa's place? Doesn’t she live alone?
Soohyeon: Umm... Sometimes she has guests over!
Soohyeon: Tindoiimu, where are you going?
Tindoiimu: ...Anywhere but here.
Soohyeon: Hold on, Tindoiimu—!!

Toyokuni: Stop, Soohyeon.
She needs some alone time, don’t you get it?
Soohyeon: Toyokuni...
Toyokuni: I know you want to make her feel better, but you need to know when to let up. Going now would only make things worse.
Soohyeon: ......
Soohyeon: But... but this is all our fault...
Toyokuni: —Soohyeon.
Soohyeon: Just... let me try one more time! Just one more time!
Soohyeon: Tindoiimu, please wait!
Soohyeon: —I’m sorry! I’m really sorry!
Tindoiimu: You’ve already apologized. I got it.
Soohyeon: Because all I can do is apologize!
Soohyeon: I... I mean, I know I have no right to even say I’m sorry, but...
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: I’m ashamed of the Alliance too, I really am. I'm ashamed of my home.
Soohyeon: Not only the way they treat the Insect Tribe, but also the way they treat people like me... They’ve forced everyone into hiding.
Tindoiimu: (People like her? Hiding? What does she...)

Soohyeon: I hate them! I really hate them! But even then...
This is still my home.

Soohyeon: So, all I can do is apologize.
Other than saying sorry, I’m useless... completely useless.
Tindoiimu: If you’re just going to stick with the Alliance anyway, then what’s the point of saying sorry? Sorry doesn’t make things any better.
Soohyeon: —Because, this is your home, too.
Soohyeon: You grew up here in the Alliance, and yet you’ve been treated like the enemy.
Tindoiimu: ...What are you trying to say?
Soohyeon: That said, I’ve grown up in an Alliance that has you in it. And if home didn't have you, then...
Soohyeon: Then I don't know what it would be like.
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: You’re part of my home, too. And, maybe that’s a selfish thing to say, but...
Tindoiimu: ...Everyone’s dead. What, you want my forgiveness just so you can feel better about yourself?
Soohyeon: No! That’s not it... I just—
Tindoiimu: You’re right, you are selfish! You’re a hypocrite! You and everyone else from the Alliance!
Soohyeon: ......
